{
  "book": "1nephi",
  "bookName": "1 Nephi",
  "chapter": 4,
  "voice": {
    "provider": "elevenlabs",
    "voice_id": "ddDFRErfhdc2asyySOG5",
    "model_id": "eleven_multilingual_v2",
    "settings": {
      "stability": 0.5,
      "similarity_boost": 0.75,
      "style": 0.35,
      "use_speaker_boost": true
    },
    "name": "Samuel"
  },
  "pauses": {
    "line_ms": 180,
    "verse_ms": 500
  },
  "duration": 436.607,
  "lines": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 2.322,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then I spoke to my brothers, saying:",
      "verse": "4:1",
      "lineIndex": 1
    },
    {
      "start": 2.502,
      "end": 4.685,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Let us go up again to Jerusalem,",
      "verse": "4:1",
      "lineIndex": 2
    },
    {
      "start": 4.865,
      "end": 6.537,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and let us be faithful",
      "verse": "4:1",
      "lineIndex": 3
    },
    {
      "start": 6.717,
      "end": 8.9,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "in keeping the commandments of the Lord;",
      "verse": "4:1",
      "lineIndex": 4
    },
    {
      "start": 9.08,
      "end": 12.006,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "for behold he is mightier than all the earth,",
      "verse": "4:1",
      "lineIndex": 5
    },
    {
      "start": 12.186,
      "end": 15.158,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "then why not mightier than Laban and his fifty,",
      "verse": "4:1",
      "lineIndex": 6
    },
    {
      "start": 15.338,
      "end": 17.799,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "yes, or even than his tens of thousands?",
      "verse": "4:1",
      "lineIndex": 7
    },
    {
      "start": 18.479,
      "end": 20.383,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Therefore let us go up;",
      "verse": "4:2",
      "lineIndex": 8
    },
    {
      "start": 20.563,
      "end": 22.56,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "let us be strong like to Moses;",
      "verse": "4:2",
      "lineIndex": 9
    },
    {
      "start": 22.74,
      "end": 26.037,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "for he truly spoke to the waters of the Red Sea",
      "verse": "4:2",
      "lineIndex": 10
    },
    {
      "start": 26.217,
      "end": 28.353,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and they divided this way and that,",
      "verse": "4:2",
      "lineIndex": 11
    },
    {
      "start": 28.533,
      "end": 30.483,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and our fathers came through,",
      "verse": "4:2",
      "lineIndex": 12
    },
    {
      "start": 30.663,
      "end": 32.288,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "out of captivity,",
      "verse": "4:2",
      "lineIndex": 13
    },
    {
      "start": 32.468,
      "end": 34.001,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "on dry ground,",
      "verse": "4:2",
      "lineIndex": 14
    },
    {
      "start": 34.181,
      "end": 36.457,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and the armies of Pharaoh followed",
      "verse": "4:2",
      "lineIndex": 15
    },
    {
      "start": 36.637,
      "end": 39.47,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and were drowned in the waters of the Red Sea.",
      "verse": "4:2",
      "lineIndex": 16
    },
    {
      "start": 40.15,
      "end": 42.518,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Now behold you know that this is true;",
      "verse": "4:3",
      "lineIndex": 17
    },
    {
      "start": 42.698,
      "end": 45.577,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and you also know that an angel has spoken to you;",
      "verse": "4:3",
      "lineIndex": 18
    },
    {
      "start": 45.757,
      "end": 47.104,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "so can you doubt?",
      "verse": "4:3",
      "lineIndex": 19
    },
    {
      "start": 47.284,
      "end": 48.584,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Let us go up;",
      "verse": "4:3",
      "lineIndex": 20
    },
    {
      "start": 48.764,
      "end": 50.947,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "the Lord is able to deliver us,",
      "verse": "4:3",
      "lineIndex": 21
    },
    {
      "start": 51.127,
      "end": 52.706,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "even as our fathers,",
      "verse": "4:3",
      "lineIndex": 22
    },
    {
      "start": 52.886,
      "end": 54.511,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and to destroy Laban,",
      "verse": "4:3",
      "lineIndex": 23
    },
    {
      "start": 54.691,
      "end": 56.131,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "even as the Egyptians.",
      "verse": "4:3",
      "lineIndex": 24
    },
    {
      "start": 56.811,
      "end": 60.155,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Now when I had spoken these words, they were yet angry,",
      "verse": "4:4",
      "lineIndex": 26
    },
    {
      "start": 60.335,
      "end": 62.611,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and did still continue to complain;",
      "verse": "4:4",
      "lineIndex": 27
    },
    {
      "start": 62.791,
      "end": 64.602,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "but they followed me up",
      "verse": "4:4",
      "lineIndex": 28
    },
    {
      "start": 64.782,
      "end": 67.336,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "until we came without the walls of Jerusalem.",
      "verse": "4:4",
      "lineIndex": 29
    },
    {
      "start": 68.016,
      "end": 69.781,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And it was by night;",
      "verse": "4:5",
      "lineIndex": 30
    },
    {
      "start": 69.961,
      "end": 73.862,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and I caused that they should hide themselves without the walls.",
      "verse": "4:5",
      "lineIndex": 31
    },
    {
      "start": 74.042,
      "end": 76.225,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And after they had hid themselves,",
      "verse": "4:5",
      "lineIndex": 32
    },
    {
      "start": 76.405,
      "end": 78.634,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "I, Nephi, crept into the city",
      "verse": "4:5",
      "lineIndex": 33
    },
    {
      "start": 78.814,
      "end": 81.508,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and went forth towards the house of Laban.",
      "verse": "4:5",
      "lineIndex": 34
    },
    {
      "start": 82.188,
      "end": 84.231,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And I was led by the Spirit,",
      "verse": "4:6",
      "lineIndex": 35
    },
    {
      "start": 84.411,
      "end": 87.476,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "not knowing beforehand the things which I should do.",
      "verse": "4:6",
      "lineIndex": 36
    },
    {
      "start": 88.156,
      "end": 89.689,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "But I went forth,",
      "verse": "4:7",
      "lineIndex": 37
    },
    {
      "start": 89.869,
      "end": 92.377,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and as I came near to the house of Laban",
      "verse": "4:7",
      "lineIndex": 38
    },
    {
      "start": 92.557,
      "end": 93.904,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "I saw a man,",
      "verse": "4:7",
      "lineIndex": 39
    },
    {
      "start": 94.084,
      "end": 96.592,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and he had fallen to the earth before me,",
      "verse": "4:7",
      "lineIndex": 40
    },
    {
      "start": 96.772,
      "end": 98.815,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "for he was drunken with wine.",
      "verse": "4:7",
      "lineIndex": 41
    },
    {
      "start": 99.495,
      "end": 102.839,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And when I came to him I found that it was Laban.",
      "verse": "4:8",
      "lineIndex": 42
    },
    {
      "start": 103.519,
      "end": 105.052,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And I saw his sword,",
      "verse": "4:9",
      "lineIndex": 43
    },
    {
      "start": 105.232,
      "end": 107.693,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and I drew it forth from the sheath of it;",
      "verse": "4:9",
      "lineIndex": 44
    },
    {
      "start": 107.873,
      "end": 110.241,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and the hilt of it was of pure gold,",
      "verse": "4:9",
      "lineIndex": 45
    },
    {
      "start": 110.421,
      "end": 112.929,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and the workmanship of it was very fine,",
      "verse": "4:9",
      "lineIndex": 46
    },
    {
      "start": 113.109,
      "end": 115.199,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and I saw that the blade of it",
      "verse": "4:9",
      "lineIndex": 47
    },
    {
      "start": 115.379,
      "end": 117.655,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "was of the most precious steel.",
      "verse": "4:9",
      "lineIndex": 48
    },
    {
      "start": 118.335,
      "end": 120.936,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then I was compelled by the Spirit",
      "verse": "4:10",
      "lineIndex": 50
    },
    {
      "start": 121.116,
      "end": 122.741,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that I should kill Laban;",
      "verse": "4:10",
      "lineIndex": 51
    },
    {
      "start": 122.921,
      "end": 124.779,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "but I said in my heart:",
      "verse": "4:10",
      "lineIndex": 52
    },
    {
      "start": 124.959,
      "end": 127.792,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Never at any time have I shed the blood of man.",
      "verse": "4:10",
      "lineIndex": 53
    },
    {
      "start": 127.972,
      "end": 130.758,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And I shrank and would that I might not kill him.",
      "verse": "4:10",
      "lineIndex": 54
    },
    {
      "start": 131.438,
      "end": 133.621,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And the Spirit said to me again:",
      "verse": "4:11",
      "lineIndex": 55
    },
    {
      "start": 133.801,
      "end": 136.82,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Behold the Lord has delivered him into your hands.",
      "verse": "4:11",
      "lineIndex": 56
    },
    {
      "start": 137.0,
      "end": 141.876,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Indeed, and I also knew that he had sought to take away my own life;",
      "verse": "4:11",
      "lineIndex": 57
    },
    {
      "start": 142.056,
      "end": 145.818,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "yes, and he would not listen to the commandments of the Lord;",
      "verse": "4:11",
      "lineIndex": 58
    },
    {
      "start": 145.998,
      "end": 148.366,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and he also had taken away our property.",
      "verse": "4:11",
      "lineIndex": 59
    },
    {
      "start": 149.046,
      "end": 151.089,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then the Spirit said to me again:",
      "verse": "4:12",
      "lineIndex": 60
    },
    {
      "start": 151.269,
      "end": 152.198,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Kill him,",
      "verse": "4:12",
      "lineIndex": 61
    },
    {
      "start": 152.378,
      "end": 155.629,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "for the Lord has delivered him into your hands;",
      "verse": "4:12",
      "lineIndex": 62
    },
    {
      "start": 156.309,
      "end": 158.399,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Behold the Lord kills the wicked",
      "verse": "4:13",
      "lineIndex": 63
    },
    {
      "start": 158.579,
      "end": 161.087,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "to bring forth his righteous purposes.",
      "verse": "4:13",
      "lineIndex": 64
    },
    {
      "start": 161.267,
      "end": 163.589,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "It is better that one man should perish",
      "verse": "4:13",
      "lineIndex": 65
    },
    {
      "start": 163.769,
      "end": 166.973,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "than that a nation should dwindle and perish in unbelief.",
      "verse": "4:13",
      "lineIndex": 66
    },
    {
      "start": 167.653,
      "end": 170.3,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And now, when I, Nephi, had heard these words,",
      "verse": "4:14",
      "lineIndex": 67
    },
    {
      "start": 170.48,
      "end": 172.848,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "I remembered the words of the Lord",
      "verse": "4:14",
      "lineIndex": 68
    },
    {
      "start": 173.028,
      "end": 176.372,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "which he spoke to me in the wilderness, saying that:",
      "verse": "4:14",
      "lineIndex": 69
    },
    {
      "start": 176.552,
      "end": 179.849,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "To the degree that your seed shall keep my commandments,",
      "verse": "4:14",
      "lineIndex": 70
    },
    {
      "start": 180.029,
      "end": 182.537,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "they shall prosper in the land of promise.",
      "verse": "4:14",
      "lineIndex": 71
    },
    {
      "start": 183.217,
      "end": 185.214,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Indeed, and I also thought",
      "verse": "4:15",
      "lineIndex": 72
    },
    {
      "start": 185.394,
      "end": 188.134,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that they could not keep the commandments of the Lord",
      "verse": "4:15",
      "lineIndex": 73
    },
    {
      "start": 188.314,
      "end": 190.357,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "according to the law of Moses,",
      "verse": "4:15",
      "lineIndex": 74
    },
    {
      "start": 190.537,
      "end": 192.441,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "save they should have the law.",
      "verse": "4:15",
      "lineIndex": 75
    },
    {
      "start": 193.121,
      "end": 197.904,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And I also knew that the law was engraved upon the plates of brass.",
      "verse": "4:16",
      "lineIndex": 76
    },
    {
      "start": 198.584,
      "end": 201.928,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And again, I knew that the Lord had delivered Laban",
      "verse": "4:17",
      "lineIndex": 77
    },
    {
      "start": 202.108,
      "end": 204.058,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "into my hands for this cause\u2014",
      "verse": "4:17",
      "lineIndex": 78
    },
    {
      "start": 204.238,
      "end": 206.514,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that I might obtain the records",
      "verse": "4:17",
      "lineIndex": 79
    },
    {
      "start": 206.694,
      "end": 208.459,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "according to his commandments.",
      "verse": "4:17",
      "lineIndex": 80
    },
    {
      "start": 209.139,
      "end": 211.786,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Therefore I obeyed the voice of the Spirit,",
      "verse": "4:18",
      "lineIndex": 81
    },
    {
      "start": 211.966,
      "end": 214.567,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and took Laban by the hair of the head,",
      "verse": "4:18",
      "lineIndex": 82
    },
    {
      "start": 214.747,
      "end": 217.348,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and I struck off his head with his own sword.",
      "verse": "4:18",
      "lineIndex": 83
    },
    {
      "start": 218.028,
      "end": 221.093,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And after I had struck off his head with his own sword,",
      "verse": "4:19",
      "lineIndex": 84
    },
    {
      "start": 221.273,
      "end": 224.802,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "I took the garments of Laban and put them upon my own body;",
      "verse": "4:19",
      "lineIndex": 85
    },
    {
      "start": 224.982,
      "end": 227.072,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "indeed, even every bit;",
      "verse": "4:19",
      "lineIndex": 86
    },
    {
      "start": 227.252,
      "end": 229.946,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and I did strap on his armor about my waist.",
      "verse": "4:19",
      "lineIndex": 87
    },
    {
      "start": 230.626,
      "end": 232.344,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And after I had done this,",
      "verse": "4:20",
      "lineIndex": 89
    },
    {
      "start": 232.524,
      "end": 234.8,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "I went forth to the treasury of Laban.",
      "verse": "4:20",
      "lineIndex": 90
    },
    {
      "start": 234.98,
      "end": 237.906,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And as I went forth towards the treasury of Laban,",
      "verse": "4:20",
      "lineIndex": 91
    },
    {
      "start": 238.086,
      "end": 241.987,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "behold, I saw the servant of Laban who had the keys of the treasury.",
      "verse": "4:20",
      "lineIndex": 92
    },
    {
      "start": 242.167,
      "end": 244.721,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And I commanded him in the voice of Laban,",
      "verse": "4:20",
      "lineIndex": 93
    },
    {
      "start": 244.901,
      "end": 247.641,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that he should go with me into the treasury.",
      "verse": "4:20",
      "lineIndex": 94
    },
    {
      "start": 248.321,
      "end": 251.386,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And he supposed me to be his master, Laban,",
      "verse": "4:21",
      "lineIndex": 95
    },
    {
      "start": 251.566,
      "end": 253.145,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "for he saw the garments",
      "verse": "4:21",
      "lineIndex": 96
    },
    {
      "start": 253.325,
      "end": 255.879,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and also the sword fastened about my waist.",
      "verse": "4:21",
      "lineIndex": 97
    },
    {
      "start": 256.559,
      "end": 259.578,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And he spoke to me concerning the elders of the Jews,",
      "verse": "4:22",
      "lineIndex": 98
    },
    {
      "start": 259.758,
      "end": 262.08,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "he knowing that his master, Laban,",
      "verse": "4:22",
      "lineIndex": 99
    },
    {
      "start": 262.26,
      "end": 264.675,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "had been out by night among them.",
      "verse": "4:22",
      "lineIndex": 100
    },
    {
      "start": 265.355,
      "end": 268.42,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And I spoke to him as if it had been Laban.",
      "verse": "4:23",
      "lineIndex": 101
    },
    {
      "start": 269.1,
      "end": 270.818,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And I also spoke to him",
      "verse": "4:24",
      "lineIndex": 102
    },
    {
      "start": 270.998,
      "end": 273.181,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that I should carry the engravings,",
      "verse": "4:24",
      "lineIndex": 103
    },
    {
      "start": 273.361,
      "end": 275.776,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "which were upon the plates of brass,",
      "verse": "4:24",
      "lineIndex": 104
    },
    {
      "start": 275.956,
      "end": 277.489,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "to my elder brothers,",
      "verse": "4:24",
      "lineIndex": 105
    },
    {
      "start": 277.669,
      "end": 279.434,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "who were without the walls.",
      "verse": "4:24",
      "lineIndex": 106
    },
    {
      "start": 280.114,
      "end": 282.575,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And I also told him that he should follow me.",
      "verse": "4:25",
      "lineIndex": 107
    },
    {
      "start": 283.255,
      "end": 287.202,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And he, supposing that I spoke of the brothers of the church,",
      "verse": "4:26",
      "lineIndex": 108
    },
    {
      "start": 287.382,
      "end": 290.493,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and that I was truly that Laban whom I had killed,",
      "verse": "4:26",
      "lineIndex": 109
    },
    {
      "start": 290.673,
      "end": 292.02,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "so he followed me.",
      "verse": "4:26",
      "lineIndex": 110
    },
    {
      "start": 292.7,
      "end": 296.369,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And he spoke to me many times concerning the elders of the Jews,",
      "verse": "4:27",
      "lineIndex": 111
    },
    {
      "start": 296.549,
      "end": 298.778,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "as I went forth to my brothers,",
      "verse": "4:27",
      "lineIndex": 112
    },
    {
      "start": 298.958,
      "end": 300.723,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "who were without the walls.",
      "verse": "4:27",
      "lineIndex": 113
    },
    {
      "start": 301.403,
      "end": 303.307,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then when Laman saw me",
      "verse": "4:28",
      "lineIndex": 114
    },
    {
      "start": 303.487,
      "end": 305.159,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "he was very frightened,",
      "verse": "4:28",
      "lineIndex": 115
    },
    {
      "start": 305.339,
      "end": 307.104,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and also Lemuel and Sam.",
      "verse": "4:28",
      "lineIndex": 116
    },
    {
      "start": 307.284,
      "end": 309.792,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And they fled from before my presence;",
      "verse": "4:28",
      "lineIndex": 117
    },
    {
      "start": 309.972,
      "end": 312.062,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "for they supposed it was Laban,",
      "verse": "4:28",
      "lineIndex": 118
    },
    {
      "start": 312.242,
      "end": 313.914,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and that he had killed me",
      "verse": "4:28",
      "lineIndex": 119
    },
    {
      "start": 314.094,
      "end": 316.88,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and had sought to take away their lives also.",
      "verse": "4:28",
      "lineIndex": 120
    },
    {
      "start": 317.56,
      "end": 319.51,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then I called after them,",
      "verse": "4:29",
      "lineIndex": 121
    },
    {
      "start": 319.69,
      "end": 321.037,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and they heard me;",
      "verse": "4:29",
      "lineIndex": 122
    },
    {
      "start": 321.217,
      "end": 323.539,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "so they ceased to flee from my presence.",
      "verse": "4:29",
      "lineIndex": 123
    },
    {
      "start": 324.219,
      "end": 327.284,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then when the servant of Laban saw my brothers",
      "verse": "4:30",
      "lineIndex": 125
    },
    {
      "start": 327.464,
      "end": 329.043,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "he began to tremble,",
      "verse": "4:30",
      "lineIndex": 126
    },
    {
      "start": 329.223,
      "end": 331.591,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and was about to flee from before me",
      "verse": "4:30",
      "lineIndex": 127
    },
    {
      "start": 331.771,
      "end": 334.047,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and return to the city of Jerusalem.",
      "verse": "4:30",
      "lineIndex": 128
    },
    {
      "start": 334.727,
      "end": 338.117,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And now I, Nephi, being a man large in stature,",
      "verse": "4:31",
      "lineIndex": 129
    },
    {
      "start": 338.297,
      "end": 341.501,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and also having received much strength of the Lord,",
      "verse": "4:31",
      "lineIndex": 130
    },
    {
      "start": 341.681,
      "end": 344.607,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "therefore I seized upon the servant of Laban,",
      "verse": "4:31",
      "lineIndex": 131
    },
    {
      "start": 344.787,
      "end": 345.948,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and held him,",
      "verse": "4:31",
      "lineIndex": 132
    },
    {
      "start": 346.128,
      "end": 347.614,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that he should not flee.",
      "verse": "4:31",
      "lineIndex": 133
    },
    {
      "start": 348.294,
      "end": 350.105,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then I spoke with him,",
      "verse": "4:32",
      "lineIndex": 134
    },
    {
      "start": 350.285,
      "end": 352.375,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "if he would listen to my words,",
      "verse": "4:32",
      "lineIndex": 135
    },
    {
      "start": 352.555,
      "end": 353.995,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "as the Lord lives,",
      "verse": "4:32",
      "lineIndex": 136
    },
    {
      "start": 354.175,
      "end": 355.568,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and as I live,",
      "verse": "4:32",
      "lineIndex": 137
    },
    {
      "start": 355.748,
      "end": 358.859,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "even so that if he would listen to our words,",
      "verse": "4:32",
      "lineIndex": 138
    },
    {
      "start": 359.039,
      "end": 360.664,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "we would spare his life.",
      "verse": "4:32",
      "lineIndex": 139
    },
    {
      "start": 361.344,
      "end": 362.877,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And I spoke to him,",
      "verse": "4:33",
      "lineIndex": 140
    },
    {
      "start": 363.057,
      "end": 364.45,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "even with an oath,",
      "verse": "4:33",
      "lineIndex": 141
    },
    {
      "start": 364.63,
      "end": 366.348,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that he need not fear;",
      "verse": "4:33",
      "lineIndex": 142
    },
    {
      "start": 366.528,
      "end": 368.804,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that he should be a free man like to us",
      "verse": "4:33",
      "lineIndex": 143
    },
    {
      "start": 368.984,
      "end": 372.049,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "if he would go down in the wilderness with us.",
      "verse": "4:33",
      "lineIndex": 144
    },
    {
      "start": 372.729,
      "end": 374.912,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And I also spoke to him, saying:",
      "verse": "4:34",
      "lineIndex": 145
    },
    {
      "start": 375.092,
      "end": 378.25,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Surely the Lord has commanded us to do this thing;",
      "verse": "4:34",
      "lineIndex": 146
    },
    {
      "start": 378.43,
      "end": 380.288,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and shall we not be diligent",
      "verse": "4:34",
      "lineIndex": 147
    },
    {
      "start": 380.468,
      "end": 382.697,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "in keeping the commandments of the Lord?",
      "verse": "4:34",
      "lineIndex": 148
    },
    {
      "start": 382.877,
      "end": 384.874,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Therefore, if you will go down",
      "verse": "4:34",
      "lineIndex": 149
    },
    {
      "start": 385.054,
      "end": 387.608,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "into the wilderness to my father",
      "verse": "4:34",
      "lineIndex": 150
    },
    {
      "start": 387.788,
      "end": 389.646,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "you shall have place with us.",
      "verse": "4:34",
      "lineIndex": 151
    },
    {
      "start": 390.326,
      "end": 393.484,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then Zoram took courage at the words which I spoke.",
      "verse": "4:35",
      "lineIndex": 152
    },
    {
      "start": 393.664,
      "end": 395.94,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Now Zoram was the name of the servant;",
      "verse": "4:35",
      "lineIndex": 153
    },
    {
      "start": 396.12,
      "end": 398.535,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and he promised that he would go down",
      "verse": "4:35",
      "lineIndex": 154
    },
    {
      "start": 398.715,
      "end": 400.805,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "into the wilderness to our father.",
      "verse": "4:35",
      "lineIndex": 155
    },
    {
      "start": 400.985,
      "end": 403.818,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Indeed, and he also made an oath to us",
      "verse": "4:35",
      "lineIndex": 156
    },
    {
      "start": 403.998,
      "end": 406.831,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that he would stay with us from that time forth.",
      "verse": "4:35",
      "lineIndex": 157
    },
    {
      "start": 407.511,
      "end": 411.644,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "Now we were desirous that he should stay with us for this cause,",
      "verse": "4:36",
      "lineIndex": 158
    },
    {
      "start": 411.824,
      "end": 416.607,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "that the Jews might not know concerning our flight into the wilderness,",
      "verse": "4:36",
      "lineIndex": 159
    },
    {
      "start": 416.787,
      "end": 419.898,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "for fear that they should pursue us and destroy us.",
      "verse": "4:36",
      "lineIndex": 160
    },
    {
      "start": 420.578,
      "end": 423.225,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then when Zoram had made an oath to us,",
      "verse": "4:37",
      "lineIndex": 161
    },
    {
      "start": 423.405,
      "end": 425.959,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "our fears ceased concerning him.",
      "verse": "4:37",
      "lineIndex": 162
    },
    {
      "start": 426.639,
      "end": 428.729,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "And then we took the plates of brass",
      "verse": "4:38",
      "lineIndex": 163
    },
    {
      "start": 428.909,
      "end": 430.767,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and the servant of Laban,",
      "verse": "4:38",
      "lineIndex": 164
    },
    {
      "start": 430.947,
      "end": 433.223,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and departed into the wilderness,",
      "verse": "4:38",
      "lineIndex": 165
    },
    {
      "start": 433.403,
      "end": 435.957,
      "type": "line",
      "text": "and journeyed to the tent of our father.",
      "verse": "4:38",
      "lineIndex": 166
    }
  ]
}